THE SA Football Association (Safa) and Kaizer Chiefs have paid tribute to the Khune family following Itumeleng Khune's sister's passing. Mapula Khune, youngster sister to Itumeleng, died on Thursday. Bafana Bafana goalkeeper Itumeleng Khune's sister dies "On behalf of Safa and the football fraternity, I would like to offer my condolences to the Khune family on their loss. We hope the Almighty will give you strength during this difficult period. May the soul of Mapula rest in peace," said Safa President Dr. Danny Jordaan. Chiefs spokesperson Vina Maphosa said: "From Kaizer Chiefs Football Club, we send our condolences to Itumeleng Khune and his family. "We, as the club, have mechanisms to work with our players when they are faced with challenges. We've instituted all that to support the player and we are with the family during this trying time." Heartfelt condolences @IIKHUNE_32_16 Praying for you and the family. Praying for strength, for healing ?? ????  Rest In Peace Baby Sister. No Meiki I am not okay so it will never be okay Pantsa. I love you with all my heart. I can’t believe I won’t hear you say ‘My Ausi’ ‘Big Sis’ or ‘My Suster’ again.What a mess. Ke a painelwa ???????????????????????????????????????????? pic.twitter.com/WlktsF57Bi   